<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" role="crossHeading" topic="editorialNotes" id="iddd44a467-3a6f-11f1-8fa0-c065796a7f06"><heading class="centered"><b>Editorial Notes</b></heading></note>
<note style="-uslm-lc:I75" topic="referencesInText" id="iddd44a468-3a6f-11f1-8fa0-c065796a7f06">
<heading class="centered smallCaps">References in Text</heading><p style="-uslm-lc:I21" class="indent0">This chapter, referred to in text, was in the original “this Act”, meaning <ref href="/us/pl/108/100">Pub. L. 108–100</ref>, <date date="2003-10-28">Oct. 28, 2003</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/117/1177">117 Stat. 1177</ref>, which is classified generally to this chapter. For complete classification of this Act to the Code, see Short Title note set out under <ref href="/us/usc/t12/s5001">section 5001 of this title</ref> and Tables.</p>
</note>
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" role="crossHeading" topic="statutoryNotes" id="iddd44a469-3a6f-11f1-8fa0-c065796a7f06"><heading class="centered"><b>Statutory Notes and Related Subsidiaries</b></heading></note>
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" topic="effectiveDate" id="iddd44a46a-3a6f-11f1-8fa0-c065796a7f06"><heading class="centered smallCaps">Effective Date</heading><p style="-uslm-lc:I21" class="indent0">Section effective at the end of the 12-month period beginning on <date date="2003-10-28">Oct. 28, 2003</date>, see <ref href="/us/pl/108/100/s20">section 20 of Pub. L. 108–100</ref>, set out as a note under <ref href="/us/usc/t12/s5001">section 5001 of this title</ref>.</p>
</note>
</notes>
